# 🚀 15 Days of Playwright

A 15-day deep dive into Microsoft Playwright, exploring its powerful features for browser automation, testing, and web scraping.

[![Playwright Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/Playwright-1.40+-blue)](https://playwright.dev)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

## 📖 Motivation

As modern web applications become increasingly complex, having reliable testing tools is crucial. Playwright emerged as a next-generation solution addressing pain points from older tools like Selenium and Cypress:

- **True cross-browser testing** (Chromium, Firefox, WebKit)
- **Auto-waiting** and **web-first assertions**
- **Mobile device emulation** out-of-the-box
- **Unified API** across all browsers

This project documents my 15-day journey mastering Playwright's capabilities while building practical test automation solutions.

## 🛠 Technologies Used

| Technology     | Purpose                        |
| -------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Playwright     | Core test automation framework |
| Node.js (v20+) | JavaScript runtime             |
| GitHub Actions | CI/CD integration              |
| Allure Reports | Test reporting (optional)      |

